{
  "texts": [
    "The main idea is to use a Conditional Random Field (CRF) variational family.",
    "The models learns recognition networks that output potential graphical models instead of outputting the complete variational distribution's parameters directly.",
    "These potential models are then used in graphical model inference algorithms in place of the observation likelihoods.",
    "SVAE provides a rich latent representations, and enables fast variational inference, while enhancing interpretability.",
    "Other combination alternative to enhance interpretability is presented in Chen et al. (2023), who combines Bayesian estimators and interactive features with ML models to improve predictive performance, in a way that these models become transparent to understand."
  ]
}